### 4. LINKS — Relationships

**Q: How do entities relate to each other?**

**A:**

```
┌─────────┐       ┌─────────┐
│  User   │───────│ Booking │
└─────────┘  1:N  └─────────┘
                       │
                       │ N:1
                       ▼
                  ┌─────────┐
                  │ Concert │
                  └─────────┘
                       │
                       │ N:1
                       ▼
                  ┌─────────┐
                  │  Venue  │
                  └─────────┘
                       │
                       │ 1:N
                       ▼
                  ┌─────────┐
                  │  Seat   │
                  └─────────┘
```

| Relationship | Type | Description |
|--------------|------|-------------|
| User → Booking | 1:N | One user, many bookings |
| Booking → Concert | N:1 | Many bookings for one concert |
| Concert → Venue | N:1 | Many concerts at one venue |
| Venue → Seat | 1:N | One venue, many seats |
| Booking → Seat | 1:N | One booking, multiple seats |

---

### 5. LIMITS — Constraints

**Q: What constraints should the system enforce?**

**A:**

| Constraint | Value | Reason |
|------------|-------|--------|
| Max seats per booking | 10 | Prevent bulk buying/scalping |
| Seat lock duration | 10 minutes | Give time for payment, but not too long |
| Advance booking | Up to 30 days before | Standard policy |
| Same-day booking | Not allowed | Logistics |

---

### 6. FAILS — What Can Go Wrong?

**Q: What are the failure scenarios?**

**A:**

| Scenario | Handling |
|----------|----------|
| **Two users select same seat** | First to lock wins. Second sees "Seat unavailable" |
| **Lock expires (no payment)** | Seats automatically released back to AVAILABLE |
| **Payment fails** | Seats released, user can retry |
| **User cancels after booking** | Refund policy applies, seats released |

### Cancellation Policy:

| When | Refund |
|------|--------|
| More than 24 hours before concert | Full refund |
| Within 24 hours | No refund |
| After concert started | No refund |

---

### 7. SCALE — Extensions

**Q: Single system or distributed?**

**A:**
- For interview: **Single system** (simpler)
- If asked about scale: "I'd add a SeatLockManager service, use Redis for locks, and a message queue for booking events"

